item.title: Need Help Compiling
item.dc:creator: @nickog15 nickog15
item.description:
@nickog15 wrote:

It depends on what you are channg the names in, that message you got just says that it was successfully complied, and to change the name of something in your server you just search for it. Lets say mine was named “PostScape” then i would look for “PostScape” and remove “PostScape” and replace it with the name of my server “PreviewScape”. You would also need to do this with the names of the owner of the server. But if you are here to learn, then this is just leeching someones work, unless you are going to re-write code, fix bugs, put lots of new stuff in, and please give credit to the owner of the work when/if you release it in the downloads section. And once you are done always compile! The more often you do it the less code you have to go though if you get a error!
